  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Capacity reinforcement on social inclusion and intercultural competences for a culture of peace</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ensuring united and stable society based on mutual respect is one of the key development goals of ethnically and culturally diverse countries such as Fiji and the Solomon Islands who experienced a period of social unrest. Persons with disabilities (PWDs) is another marginalised population facing exclusion &amp; being disproportionately represented among the region&apos;s unemployed and poor asreflected in the Pacific Framework for the Rights of PWDs 2016-25 calling for an inclusive, barrier-free, and rights-based society for PWDs.
The project reinforces the institutional capacity of policy-makers and civil society organisations in order to promote intercultural competences; and bridges the gap between policy-makers and the academia in understanding the vulnerability of PWDs.</narrative>
  </description>
